#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.31:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.31:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga "
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Sabrahmakasutta "
msgstr "31. With Brahmā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.132, sc1
msgctxt "an3.31:1.1"
msgid "“Sabrahmakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with Brahmā. "

msgctxt "an3.31:1.2"
msgid "Sapubbācariyakāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti. "
msgstr "A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with the first teachers. "

msgctxt "an3.31:1.3"
msgid "Sāhuneyyāni, bhikkhave, tāni kulāni yesaṃ puttānaṃ mātāpitaro ajjhāgāre pūjitā honti. "
msgstr "A family where the children honor their parents in their home is said to live with those worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.31:1.4"
msgid "‘Brahmā’ti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Brahmā’ is a term for your parents. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.31:1.5"
msgid "‘Pubbācariyā’ti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘First teachers’ is a term for your parents. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.31:1.6"
msgid "‘Āhuneyyā’ti, bhikkhave, mātāpitūnaṃ etaṃ adhivacanaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods’ is a term for your parents. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.31:1.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.31:1.8"
msgid "Bahukārā, bhikkhave, mātāpitaro puttānaṃ, āpādakā posakā, imassa lokassa dassetāroti. "
msgstr "Parents are very helpful to their children, they raise them, nurture them, and show them the world. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.31:2.1"
msgid "Brahmāti mātāpitaro, "
msgstr "Parents are said to be ‘Brahmā’ "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:2.2"
msgid "pubbācariyāti vuccare; "
msgstr "and ‘first teachers’, it’s said. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:2.3"
msgid "Āhuneyyā ca puttānaṃ, "
msgstr "They’re worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods from their children, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:2.4"
msgid "pajāya anukampakā. "
msgstr "for they love their offspring. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.31:3.1"
msgid "Tasmā hi ne namasseyya, "
msgstr "Therefore an astute person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:3.2"
msgid "sakkareyya ca paṇḍito; "
msgstr "would revere them and honor them "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:3.3"
msgid "Annena atha pānena, "
msgstr "with food and drink, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:3.4"
msgid "vatthena sayanena ca; "
msgstr "clothes and bedding, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nhāpanena → nahāpanena (bj)
msgctxt "an3.31:3.5"
msgid "Ucchādanena nhāpanena, "
msgstr "anointing and bathing, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:3.6"
msgid "pādānaṃ dhovanena ca. "
msgstr "and by washing their feet. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.31:4.1"
msgid "Tāya naṃ pāricariyāya, "
msgstr "Because they look after "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.31:4.2"
msgid "mātāpitūsu paṇḍitā; "
msgstr "their parents like this, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Idheva → idhaceva (bj)
msgctxt "an3.31:4.3"
msgid "Idheva naṃ pasaṃsanti, "
msgstr "in this life they’re praised by the astute, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sagge pamodatī”ti → sagge ca modatīti (bj)
msgctxt "an3.31:4.4"
msgid "pecca sagge pamodatī”ti. "
msgstr "and they depart to rejoice in heaven.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.31:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
